File: Janusz Walus is serving a life sentence for gunning down SA Communist Party leader Chris Hani in 1993. JOHANNESBURG - Chris Hani's killer Janusz Walus has again lost his bid for parole. He's failed to convince the Gauteng High Court in Pretoria that he should be released. READ: Justice Minister to give decision on Walus parole bid The convicted murderer is currently serving a life sentence for shooting Hani outside his Dawn Park home in 1993. The ruling upholds the refusal by Justice and Correctional Services Minister Ronald Lamola to grant Walus parole. Giving his reasons for denying parole, Lamola said the crime was intended and had the potential to bring about civil war within the republic at the time.